    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA246-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu piriviṭai melinta talaimakaḷait tōḻi vaṟpuṟīiyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante comforted HER who had become weak in the time of separation.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA246">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            iṭūuṅka ṇiṉiya paṭūun neṭuñcuvar</l>
<l>            palliyum pāṅkiṟ ṟēṟṟu maṉṟē</l>
<l>            maṉaimara nocci mīmicai mācciṉai</l>
<l>            viṉaimā ṇiruṅkuyil payiṟṟalum payiṟṟu</l>
<l>            murampuri yuḷḷamoṭu curampala nīntic </l>
<l>            ceyporuṭ kakaṉṟaṉa rāyiṉum poyyalar</l>
<l>            varuvar vāḻi tōḻi puṟaviṟ</l>
<l>            poṉvīk koṉṟaiyoṭu piṭavuttaḷai yaviḻa</l>
<l>            viṉṉicai vāṉa miraṅkumavar</l>
<l>            varutu meṉṟa paruvamō vituvē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>The gecko too in the neighbourhood makes it clear, doesn’t it,</l>
<l rend="indent">on the long wall when [its] sweet [sounds] come forth</l>
<l rend="indent">in between(?!).<note place="foot">T.V.G. reads this totally different, namely the first line referring to HER talk with the confidante, in the middle of which they would overhear auspicious words spoken by others, while the gecko in the 2nd line would crawl on the wall into the right direction (thus the explanation given for <term xml:lang="ta">pāṅkiṉ</term> by of the old commentary on AN 9.19 <term xml:lang="ta">pāṅkar palli paṭutoṟum</term>).</note></l>
<l rend="indent">While the dark Koels glorious in [their] work repeat one another</l>
<l rend="indent3">on the high big Nocci branches of the tree by the house,</l>
<l rend="indent2">even if he has departed for wealth to be made,</l>
<l rend="indent2">crossing the deserts, many, with a mind of strong desire,</l>
<l>he does not lie, he will come, oh friend.</l>
<l>As for the season he said</l>
<l rend="indent4">“we will come,</l>
<l rend="indent">when the sky roars in sweet sounds for the Piṭavu to open [its]</l>
<l rend="indent">bonds along with the gold-blossomed Laburnum in the woodland,”</l>
<l rend="indent4">[it is] this.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
